      • isChainPathMatch

        static boolean isChainPathMatch(java.util.List<java.lang.String> path1,
                                java.util.List<java.lang.String> path2)
        Return true if the path1 is equal to path2 or path1 is a sublist of path2.
        Examples: 
         
 Path1 [i1, i2, i3]      matches Path2 [i1, i2, i3] =>  true
 Path1 [i1, i2, i3]      matches Path2 [i3, i2, i1] =>  false
 Path1 [i1, i2, i3, i4]  matches Path2 [i1, i2, i3] =>  false
 Path1 [i1, i2, i3]      matches Path2 [i1, i2, i3, i4] =>  true
        Parameters:
        path1 - the path to test (mutable).
        path2 - the path to test (mutable).
        Returns:
        true or false.
